Manchester United legend Paul Scholes has said that his former club are four or five years away from winning the Premier League title. According to him, the Red Devils are far from competing for the Premier League title as the club continues to struggle. Manchester United’s recent defeats were a 4-0 loss to Liverpool and another 3-1 thrashing in the hands of Arsenal. The Red Devils legend joined talkSPORT on Tuesday morning to discuss the current state of his former club. “Next year, Manchester United will be fighting for 4th place which is not something you want. “I think we’re four or five years away from being somewhere to challenge the league!” Manchester United on Thursday announced that Ajax manager, Erik ten Hag will be in charge at Old Trafford for three years. He will take over from interim boss, Ralf Rangnick.